{title: Put On Your Old Grey Bonnet}
{artist: Jimmy Dean}
{composer: Written by Percy Wenrich and Stanley Murphy}

[G7]On an [C]old farm house veranda
There sat [D7]Silas and Miranda
[G7]Dreamin' of the days gone [C]by[G7]
He said [C]dearie don't be weary
You were [D7]always bright and cheery
Now a [G7]tear dear dims your [C]eye[G7]
She [C]said they're not tears of [D7]sadness Silas
They are [G7]tears of gladness
It was [Am]fifty years [D7]ago today we [G7]wed
Then the old [C]man's dim eyes brightened
And his [D7]stern old heart it lightened
As he [G7]turned to her and [C]said[G7]
Put on your [C]old grey bonnet
With all the [F]blue ribbons on it
While I [C]hitch [Am]old [D7]Dobbin to the shade[G7]
Through those [C]fields of clover
We'll [F]ride up to [C]Dover
[F]On our [C]gol[D7]den [G7]wedding [C]day
Repeat last verse
[F]On our [C]gol[D7]den [G7]wedding [C]day